The paper deals with style transfer, which is a topic that falls under computer vision and graphics. The paper proposes a novel transfer framework that jointly analyzes and aligns exchangeable features extracted from content and style image pair. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new loss function, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
